President Obama announced the members of the National Commission on the BP Deepwater Horizon Oil Spill and Offshore Drilling. The commission, created by executive order, is tasked with providing recommendations to prevent and mitigate the impact of future oil spills from offshore drilling. The co-chairs of the commission are former Florida Governor Bob Graham and former Environmental Protection Agency Administrator William K. Reilly. The members of the commission announced include Frances G. Beinecke, Donald Boesch, Terry D. Garc√≠a, Cherry A. Murray, and Frances Ulmer. Each member brings extensive knowledge and experience to the crucial work of the commission. President Obama expressed gratitude to the members for their willingness to serve and their efforts to determine the causes of the Deepwater Horizon disaster and implement necessary safety and environmental protection measures.